Package edu.ucsb.cs56.projects.games.cs56_games_maze

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AltStepGenerator
    AltStepGenerator runs off the newest added cell then the oldest added cell each step.
    Cell
    A Cell is just an object that holds a set of coordinates (row, col) the coordinates are public instance variables and accessible by cell.row and cell.col
    GenChain
    A GenChain is a primary tool used by subclasses of MazeGenerator to carve paths through a MazeGrid.
    HighScoreSaver  
    HighScoreTable
    Class where the JTable for the High Score table is created.
    IntegerDocumentFilter
    DocumentFilter that allows only integers From: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11093326/restricting-jtextfield-input-to-integers
    MazeComponent
    A class extending JComponent that is used to draw all of the information held in a MazeGrid (the markers, as well as the remaining closed walls of each cell)
    MazeGameSave
    Serializable container for holding all necessary game state data.
    MazeGenerator
    An abstract MazeGenerator class.
    MazeGrid
    A MazeGrid holds all of the saved maze informtion.
    MazeGridTest  
    MazeGui
    Class where the MazeGui is constructed.
    MazeHighScore
    Class that holds data for one maze score.
    MazeInstructGui
    Class where the JFrame for the instructions is created.
    MazePlayer
    Class to represent active player in maze game
    MazeSettings
    Class to hold settings information for one game.
    MazeSettingsDialog
    A JDialog that displays the MazeSettingsPanel to allow settings changes
    MazeSettingsPanel
    A JPanel that has labels and fields for all settings, as well as funcitonality to writeback as necessary.
    MazeTimerBar
    Represents the control bar which contains the game timer, New Maze and Solve Maze buttons
    MultipleChainGenerator
    MultipleChainGenerator runs like a string of AltStepGenerator algorithms to create more complex mazes.
    NewStepGenerator
    NewStepGenerator runs off the newest added cell each step.
